{
  "stem": "25639.9",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I couldn't call anybody mother or father because in my-- deep down in my mind, I felt that some of my family must have survived and until-- that-- and that nobody can take that place or their places, and therefore, I-- we can get close another way, and they accepted it.",
      "word_count": 51
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Ah, Eric Berglund, my foster father and Lilly Berglund, my foster mother-- he died, by the way, a few years ago-- and their daughter is Gulan Berglund who eventually married a Jewish man.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And when I visited her the first time, that was in 1962, she showed me her kosher kitchen, [LAUGHS] and taught me-- well, wanted me to know which is the towel to be used for [HEBREW] and which towel to use for [HEBREW].",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And when I lived with her, I went with her to church, and she came with me to the synagogue, and-- and we had a wonderful, wonderful relationship.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we call each other sisters to date.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was with them for two years until-- and while I was with them, I found out about my American relatives.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My mother's sister-- two sisters and brother came to the United States before World War I.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I believe I mentioned it earlier, so excuse me.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they married and had children, so actually, I had a large family in the United States, and this is the family that stayed intact.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "My European family was decimated.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] While I was with the Swedish family, one night, I dreamt my uncle's address in St.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Louis, Missouri.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I used to know his address, everybody's addresses, because I mailed mother's letters, and I used to write little notes under her letter.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I wanted to be close.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
